I"i<p>The Chaucer estate is one of five estates listed in <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1MdX6GlaHDoBdG6CTsvjFaIuPtIa9id5O/view">Sutton’s Local Plan (2018)</a> for potential redevelopment:</p>

<p><img src="/images/suttonplan.png" alt="" /></p>

<p>It is also earmarked in Sutton’s <a href="http://sutton.addresscafe.com/app/exploreit/">Policy Map</a> as a potential renewal area:</p>

<p><img src="/images/suttonpolicymap.png" alt="" /></p>

<p>In 2013, the high-rise block on the estate was cladded with a light-blue ACU composite. Two years later, after the investigations following the Grenfell disaster, it was <a href="https://www.yourlocalguardian.co.uk/news/15387026.sutton-housing-partnership-sutton-council-and-sutton-fire-commander-meet-concerned-residents-living-in-chaucer-house-sutton/">revealed</a> that the cladding had failed safety tests.</p>

